  "body": "### Steps:\r\n1.'User A' generates a QR profile code.\r\n2. 'User B' navigates to the 'Add contact' page and scans the contact using the device's camera.\r\n3. 'User B' scans 'User A's QR code by initiating the camera from the bottom part of the QR code.\r\n\r\nSteps if the issue is not reproduced after **step 3**\r\n4. If the issue is not reproduced after step 3, 'User B' attempts to scan an invalid QR code. (example: \r\n![image](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/9b8768e7-694d-41a4-b487-1f57a04d2275)\r\n)\r\n5. 'User B' rescans the QR code of 'User A.'\r\n\r\n### Actual result:\r\nAfter scanning, the 'ENS or chat key' input field fails to adjust to the size of the fetched data. Consequently, only the second line of the chat key is visible within the input field.\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/6d3914d5-c2d4-40d7-9406-31b9c0aff933\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected result:\r\nUpon scanning a QR code, the 'ENS or chat key' input field should dynamically adjust its size to display the entire chat key,\r\n\r\n### Device:\r\nPixel 7a, Android 13\r\n\r\n\r\n### Logs:\r\n[Status-debug-logs (1).zip](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/files/13390689/Status-debug-logs.1.zip)\r\n\r\n### Additional info:\r\n- Currently, the issue reproduces randomly, occurring only when quickly initiating the camera hover from the bottom QR's edge\r\n\r\n",
