    "body": "I belive the consequenced issue is related to issue https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/issues/17943#issue-2001005728\r\n\r\n## ISSUE 2: The 'ETH' input field does not adjust its size to the scanned data from a QR code\r\n\r\n### Steps:\r\n1. Generate an ETH QR code (from Status or Metamask).\r\n2. Go to Add address to watch screen\r\n3. Scan the QR code by starting the camera from the bottom part of the QR.\r\n4. Observe the result.\r\n\r\n### Actual result:\r\n\r\nAfter scanning the QR code containing eth address, the 'ETH' input field fails to adjust to the size of the fetched data. Consequently, only the second line of the eth address is visible within the input field.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/03547f91-9e21-4d40-ad35-6cc5764f005e",
